  "standardBio": "Cloudleaper, titled among keepers as “Kitecrest Runner,” carries sudden freedom in every movement. Native to Stormspire Peaks, the species crackles through ozone and kite-silk, leaving traces that other Riftlings can follow like soft maps. Wild groups form loose bonds rather than rigid packs; a brave individual may become the emotional center of a small hearthline. They eat Stormbud eagerly and dislike food that smells of neglect or spoilage. Ancient keepers carved Cloudleaper silhouettes into travel stones, believing the species guided the lost. Modern hatcheries record them as reliable companions; their instinctive pattern recognition around Rift anomalies makes training feel like conversation. Their signature ability, Cloudleaper's Gale Slash, reflects a life shaped by Stormspire Peaks more than by arena ambition. Their quiet is mistaken for emptiness. In truth they are listening harder than louder species. Young Cloudleapers practice Cloudleaper's Gale Slash as play long before they understand battle. Adults teach by demonstration: where to rest, what to avoid, how to share warmth or shade.",
